definition.value: A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of (4Z,8E,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid bearing an additional 7-hydroxy substituent.
A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of 5E,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoic acid bearing an additional 4-hydroxy substituent.
A hydroxyoctadecatrienoic acid that consists of 10E,12Z,15Z-octadecatrienoic acid bearing an additional 9-hydroxy substituent.
An N-acylglucosamine where the N-acyl group is specified as glycoloyl and the configuration of the glucosamine is beta-D.
A hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid that consists of 5Z,8Z,11Z,13E,17Z-eicosapentaenoic acid bearing an additional 15-hydroxy substituent.

A papulacandin that is papulacandin A in which the 6-O-acylgalactosyl group is replaced by a hydrogen. It is a carbohydrate-containing antibiotic from the deuteromycetous fungus Papularia sphaerosperma which shows potent antifungal activity against Candida albicans.
A phenoxybenzoic acid in which the phenoxy group is meta to the carboxy group. It is a metabolite of pyrethroid insecticides.
A phenoxybenzoic acid in which the phenoxy group is para to the carboxy group.
An aromatic ether that is diphenyl ether in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a carboxy group.
A hydroxy-1,4-naphthoquinone that is ethane in which one of the carbons is substituted by two 3-hydroxy-1,4-naphthoquinon-2-yl groups.
An enolate anion that is the dianion obtained by the deprotonation of the enol groups of impatienol.
A phenoxybenzoic acid in which the phenoxy group is ortho to the carboxy group.
A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of 4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,15E,19Z-docosahexaenoic acid bearing an additional 17-hydroxy substituent.
An eremophilane sesquiterpenoid that is (+)-5-epi-aristolochene carrying an additional 3alpha-hydroxy substituent.
A HODE that consists of 9Z,11E-octadecadienoic acid carrying a 13-hydroxy substituent.
A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of 4Z,7Z,11E,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoic acid bearing an additional 10-hydroxy substituent.
A hydroxyoctadecatrienoic acid that consists of 9Z,11E,15Z-octadecatrienoic acid bearing an additional 13-hydroxy substituent.
An eremophilane sesquiterpenoid that is (+)-5-epi-aristolochene carrying an additional 1beta-hydroxy substituent.
An HETE having a 8-hydroxy group and (5Z)-, (9E)-, (11Z)- and (14Z)-double bonds.
A hydroxyeicosatrienoic acid that consists of 8Z,11Z,13E-icosatrienoic acid bearing an additional 15-hydroxy substituent.
A hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid that consists of 5Z,8Z,10E,14Z,17Z-icosapentaenoic acid bearing an additional 12-hydroxy substituent.
The diastereomer of 7,2'-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavanol that has 3R,4R-configuration.
A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid bearing an additional 14-hydroxy substituent.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of (3R)-7,2'-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavanol, obtained by selective protonation of the 4-hydroxy group.

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and 7-hydroxy groups of cyanidin 3-O-[6-O-(4-O-beta-D-glucosyl-p-coumaroyl)-2-O-(2-O-sinapoyl-beta-D-xylosyl)-beta-D-glucosyl]-5-O-(6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucoside).
A phosphonic acid having a 2-dimethylaminoethyl group attached to the phosphorus.

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and 7-hydroxy groups of cyanidin 3-O-[6-O-(4-O-beta-D-glucosyl-p-coumaroyl)-2-O-(beta-D-xylosyl)-beta-D-glucosyl]-5-O-(6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucoside)
A HODE that consists of (10E,12Z)-octadecadienoic acid with the hydroxy substituent located at position 9.
An organic cation obtained by abstraction of a hydride from position 4 of 7,2'-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavan. A reactive intermediate in the biosynthesis of medicarpin.
An EpDPE obtained by formal epoxidation of the 19,20-double bond of docosa-4,7,10,13,16,19-hexaenoic acid.
An epoxy fatty acid obtained by formal epoxidation of one of the double bonds of any docosahexaenoic acid.
A chromenone that is 2,3-dihydro-7H-chromen-7-one substituted at position 3 by a 2-hydroxy-4-methoxyphenyl group. A reactive intermediate in the biosynthesis of medicarpin.
A hydroxy fatty acid obtained by formal dihydroxylation across one of the double bonds of any docosahexaenoic acid.
A DiHDPA obtained by formal dihydroxylation of the 19,20-double bond of docosa-4,7,10,13,16,19-hexaenoic acid.
A diterpenoid that is the 3alpha-hydroxy-11-oxo derivative of ent-cassa-12,15-diene.
An epoxy fatty acid obtained by formal epoxidation of one of the double bonds of any octadecadienoic acid.
A diterpenoid that is ent-cassa-12,15-diene in which the hydrogen at position 3beta has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A diterpenoid that is 11-oxo-ent-cassa-12,15-diene carrying two additional alpha-hydroxy substituents at positions 2 and 3.
A hydroxy fatty acid obtained by formal dihydroxylation across one of the double bonds of any octadecadienoic acid.
A DiHOME obtained by formal dihydroxylation of the 9,10-double bond of octadeca-9,12-dienoic acid (the 12Z-geoisomer).
A phytocassane that is ent-podocarp-12-ene-3,11-dione carrying additional hydroxy, vinyl and methyl substituents at the 2alpha, 13 and 14 positions, respectively.
A DiHOME obtained by formal dihydroxylation of the 12,13-double bond of octadeca-9,12-dienoic acid (the 9Z-geoisomer).
A phytocassane that is (+)-phytocassane C which has been substituted with an additional hydroxy group at the 2alpha position.
A phytocassane that is ent-podocarp-12-ene-11-one carrying two alpha-hydroxy substituents at positions 1 and 3 as well as vinyl and beta-methyl substituents at positions 13 and 14, respectively.

A phytocassane that is (+)-phytocassane A in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been oxidised to the corresponding ketone, while the keto group at position 3 has been reduced to give the corresponding 3alpha hydroxy group.
An organic anion obtained by selective deprotonation of the 2- and 7-hydroxy groups of (2S)-versicolorone.
An optically active form of versiconal hemiacetal acetate having 2S,3S-configuration.
An optically active form of versiconal hemiacetal having 2S,3S-configuration.
An optically active form of versiconol acetate(1-) having 3S-configuration.
